A dynamin-1 that is a translation product of some mRNA whose exon structure and start site selection renders it capable of giving rise to a protein with the amino acid sequence represented by UniProtKB:P21575-3 or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. This isoform contains the a version of the first splice region, and the c version of the second splice region.

definition.value: Category=sequence. Note: PMID:9725914 describes two splicing regions for dynamin-1. The first splicing region of Dyn 1 contains either one of two sequences (a and b forms) of identical size but distinct nucleotide sequences. The second one is the region coding the C-terminus making at least four distinct tails for Dynamin-1. These consist of an a tail of 20 amino acids, a b tail of 7 amino acids, a c tail of 49 amino acids, and a d tail of 12 amino acids.

value.value: A dynamin-1 isoform ac that is encoded in the genome of mouse.

definition.value: Category=organism-sequence. Note: PMID:17525220 shows sequence of the ac isoform (nomenclature after the rat nomenclature from PMID:9725914). UniProtKB:F6W8Z8 sequence fragment provides additional experimental support for the existence of the c variant of the C-terminal of the two locations of alternative splicing in Dynamin-1. Note that this fragment sequence is equally consistent with the bc isoform since it contains only the C-terminal section containing only the second of two locations of alternative splicing.
